OL,6,FIn 2023 alone, seven people lost their
OL,7,Flives due to accidental drowning in
OL,8,Fthe East Midlands.
OL,10,FAcross the country, the number of
OL,11,Fpeople who died because of accidental
OL,12,Fdrownings increased, with 236 people
OL,13,Fdying in water across the UK last year.
OL,15,FNicola, who has set up her own
OL,16,Fcampaign called OWEN, the Open Water
OL,17,FEducational Network in memory of her
OL,18,Fson, is joining calls to warn others
OL,19,Fof the dangers of open water.
