OL,3,CMum whose son drowned saving others in
OL,4,CRiver Trent says 'don't be a hero'
OL,6,FShe said: "Don't be the hero, or be a
OL,7,Fhero from the sidelines. Had Owen
OL,8,Fknown what I'm talking about in
OL,9,Fschools we probably wouldn't have even
OL,10,Fknown about this situation because the
OL,11,Fgirls would have got out safely and
OL,12,FOwen wouldn't have got out either. I
OL,13,Fcouldn't let Owen's death be in vain.
OL,15,F"From a very young age he always said
OL,16,Fto me that he wanted to be famous. He
OL,17,Fwas a great rugby player, and we
OL,18,Falways thought it would be playing
OL,19,Frugby.
