OL,4,CRiver Trent says 'don't be a hero'
OL,6,FBryn says: "So it's really really
OL,7,Fimportant that members of the public
OL,8,Fcontact the emergency services when
OL,9,Fthey see somebody in distress, don't
OL,10,Fgo in the water themselves and try and
OL,11,Freach or throw a buoyancy aid to the
OL,12,Findividual in distress.
OL,14,F"But please, please don't enter the
OL,15,Fwater. It's a natural human reaction
OL,16,Fto try and save somebody in distress
OL,17,Fbut invariably it means we get two
OL,18,Fcasualties in the water".
